{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 1.2 The False Dichotomy\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The DeFi community assumes governance is the only alternative to centralized control. This is false. There is a third option: {\b protocols that don\u8217't need governance because they self-adjust.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A thermostat doesn\u8217't vote on the temperature. It measures conditions and responds. A healthy protocol should work the same way.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 1.3 The Bootstrapping Problem\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You can\u8217't get to zero governance from zero. At launch, parameters need setting, bugs need fixing, and adversarial conditions need responding to. Some governance is necessary initially.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The solution: start with governance, but hardcode its death. Every governance token has a half-life. Every governance function has a sunset. The protocol is born with training wheels that automatically retract.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
