{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 After 10 years, governance tokens retain less than 0.1% of their original voting power. Governance proposals require supermajority, which becomes mathematically impossible as weight approaches zero.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 2.2 Implementation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 function getVotingWeight(address voter, uint256 proposalTime) public view returns (uint256) \{\line
    uint256 balance = governanceToken.balanceOf(voter);\line
    uint256 elapsed = proposalTime - GENESIS_TIMESTAMP;\line
\line
    // Decay: weight halves every HALF_LIFE_SECONDS\line
    // Using fixed-point arithmetic to avoid floating point\line
    uint256 halvings = elapsed / HALF_LIFE_SECONDS;\line
    uint256 remainder = elapsed % HALF_LIFE_SECONDS;\line
\line
    // Integer halvings\line
    uint256 weight = balance >> halvings;  // Divide by 2^halvings\line
\line
    // Sub-halving interpolation (linear approximation)\line
    if (halvings < 64 && remainder > 0) \{\line
        uint256 nextWeight = weight >> 1;\line
        weight = weight - ((weight - nextWeight) * remainder / HALF_LIFE_SECONDS);\line
    \}\line
\line
    return weight;\line
\}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 2.3 Non-Overridable\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The decay function is immutable: - No admin key can modify HALF_LIFE_SECONDS - No governance proposal can extend the decay - No upgrade proxy can replace the decay logic - The only exception: a supermajority vote (>90% of decayed weight) can extend by ONE additional half-life period \u8212- and this extension itself decays\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
