          \u9474 ?\line
          \u9500 ?\u9472 ?\u9472 ? Parameters: PID-controlled\line
          \u9500 ?\u9472 ?\u9472 ? Disputes: Automated tribunal\line
          \u9500 ?\u9472 ?\u9472 ? Upgrades: Fork-and-compete\line
          \u9500 ?\u9472 ?\u9472 ? Security: Circuit breakers + automated monitoring\line
          \u9492 ?\u9472 ?\u9472 ? Economics: Shapley distribution + fee routing\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The protocol becomes a natural system. It responds to conditions, not opinions. It evolves through forking, not voting. It distributes value through mathematics, not politics.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This is Ungovernance. The governance that governs best governs least \u8212- and eventually, not at all.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 8. The Knowledge Primitive\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi0 {\b \u8220"Governance is a bootstrapping tool, not a destination. Hardcode its death. Let the protocol become a natural system.\u8221"}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The deeper insight: any system that can be governed can be captured. The only ungovernable system is one where governance literally does not exist. But you can\u8217't start there \u8212- you have to arrive there. The decay curve is the path.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\i The protocol becomes a natural system, not a political one. That\u8217's the endgame.}\par}
